The paper presents a new algorithm for maximum weight perfect matching on general graphs, which involves data structures and algorithms for graph traversal, matching, and scaling. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves combinatorial optimization and graph theory, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of linear programming and numerical methods, which could place it in cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper discusses the comparison with previous algorithms and the theoretical analysis of the running time, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
